    "body": "### Problem\n\nI want virtual line diagnostics for my current line, and virtual text diagnostics for the rest. \n\nI have `virtual_lines` set to `current_line = true` and `virtual_text` set to `current_line = false`\n\nThe virtual lines only show up for the current line. However,  the current line still shows virtual text:\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8f5906af-17c4-4a2b-8066-54ba19c96c62\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n\nFor `vim.diagnostic`, set the following opts (from https://github.com/codevogel/nixos/blob/3543e7b107b9eb646e71933ccd0174c915fde48f/modules/shared/mnw/nvim/lua/codevogel/config/diagnostic.lua ) :\n\n```lua\nvim.diagnostic.config({\n  severity_sort = true,\n  float = { border = \"rounded\", source = \"if_many\" },\n  signs = vim.g.have_nerd_font and {\n    text = {\n      [vim.diagnostic.severity.ERROR] = \"󰅚 \",\n      [vim.diagnostic.severity.WARN] = \"󰀪 \",\n      [vim.diagnostic.severity.INFO] = \"󰋽 \",\n      [vim.diagnostic.severity.HINT] = \"󰌶 \",\n    },\n  } or {},\n  underline = true,\n  virtual_text = {\n    current_line = false,\n  },\n  virtual_lines = {\n    current_line = true,\n  },\n})\n```\n\nOr, minimally:\n```lua\nvim.diagnostic.config({\n  virtual_text = {\n    current_line = false,\n  },\n})\n```\n\nOpen a file with diagnostic warnings.\n\nVirtual text will stay visible for the current line. \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFrom the docs ( https://neovim.io/doc/user/diagnostic.html#vim.diagnostic.Opts.VirtualText ) ;\n\n> {current_line}? (boolean) Show or hide diagnostics based on the current cursor line. If true, only diagnostics on the current cursor line are shown. If false, all diagnostics are shown except on the current cursor line. If nil, all diagnostics are shown. (default nil) \n\nSo I would expect the virtual text to appear on all lines **_but_** the current line.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.6 \n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nhaven't been able to confirm\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNixOS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.45.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nnixos, mnw",
